After half of her face was paralyzed in a car accident 20 years ago, Thailand native Malinda Herman didn’t want to show her face to anyone for some time. Her son bought her a guitar to help her through that difficult period. The now 71-year-old loves singing with her dogs and cat. 😃🎶🐶😺🎵.

'Beautiful Sunday' was written by Daniel Boone. A happy & beautiful Sunday to you all!
(Malinda Herman Official)

node.text: (Milton Keynes, England): Two brothers, Kofi and Jermaine Reed say they were at the right place at the right time this Monday afternoon when they spotted a 7yr old fall into the water in Caldecotte Lake. The pair didn't hesitate to jump in and save the boy who didn't know how to swim well... the mom who had looked away for a moment hadn't noticed her son fell in and was frazzled at the time but took to social media to find the brothers and give them a proper thank you. Now the rescuers and family are friends. The mother writes: "We were blown away. They were the nicest guys and so humble about what they did." ! 🙌🙌🙌

node.text: (Paris, France): @messynessychic who took the video and purchased purchased painting writes: "I’ve seen him frequently in the neighbourhood but it was the first time I saw him selling anything. He said he liked to paint and this was from his collection. He asked for 30 euros but I thought it was quite fine and offered 40. [...] To me, regardless of its true value, this painting is treasure, for its ability to 1) remind me of his smile when I asked if I could take his picture and 2) how many of you reached out to me and said this man had brought you to tears. All of that beautiful humanity, I can now see in this painting."

Jim McIngvale is known for his Houston based furniture store, but to many, "Mattress Mack" is known for his giving heart. He is opening up his store to any Louisiana residents affected by Hurricane Ida. He did the same in storms past including Katrina. He says it's the least he can do... and "that's what Texans do." He also has a donation drive from 830a-5:30p local time at his store today and tomorrow.
